    <note>Li(2) Xin [1031] Fujian TZ, 147.3a; XCB, 83.15a; Guangdong TZ, 14.21b. While there are no linkages noted between any of the Putian Li(2) Zhao+x, they must be related based on generational indicator and are probably grandsons of Xin, which is how they are treated. The reason that there are no links may be that the lineage segmented at this point. For example, the sons of Zhaowu [16979] are both Shi+x, whereas the son of Yuan(5) [23335] is Dun+x. Zhaowu is designated as the great grandfather who founded the family (weihu) in the 1148 jinshi listings for his great grandsons, Qing [23334] and Yuan(5). This Putian Li(2) lineage may be ancestral kin of the lineage starting with Li(2) Zongshi [10993]. CBD, 2, 845.</note>
